name: ErrorType
comment: Instances of the enumeration ErrorType represent the type of an analyzer/analyzer.ErrorCode.

COMPILE_TIME_ERROR.name: COMPILE_TIME_ERROR
COMPILE_TIME_ERROR.comment: Compile-time errors are errors that preclude execution. A compile time error must be reported by a Dart compiler before the erroneous code is executed.

HINT.name: HINT
HINT.comment: Extra analysis run over the code to follow best practices, which are not in the Dart Language Specification.

PUB_SUGGESTION.name: PUB_SUGGESTION
PUB_SUGGESTION.comment: Suggestions made in situations where the user has deviated from recommended pub programming practices.

STATIC_TYPE_WARNING.name: STATIC_TYPE_WARNING
STATIC_TYPE_WARNING.comment: Many, but not all, static warnings relate to types, in which case they are known as static type warnings.

STATIC_WARNING.name: STATIC_WARNING
STATIC_WARNING.comment: Static warnings are those warnings reported by the static checker. They have no effect on execution. Static warnings must be provided by Dart compilers used during development.

SYNTACTIC_ERROR.name: SYNTACTIC_ERROR
SYNTACTIC_ERROR.comment: Syntactic errors are errors produced as a result of input that does not conform to the grammar.

severity.name: severity
severity.comment: The severity of this type of error.

name.name: name
name.comment: The name of this enum constant, as declared in the enum declaration.

constructors.comment:
Initialize a newly created error type to have the given severity.

@param severity the severity of this type of error

hashCode.name: hashCode
hashCode.comment:
Get a hash code for this object.

All objects have hash codes. Hash codes are guaranteed to be the same for objects that are equal when compared using the equality operator ==. Other than that there are no guarantees about the hash codes. They will not be consistent between runs and there are no distribution guarantees.

If a subclass overrides analyzer/analyzer.ErrorType.hashCode it should override the equality operator as well to maintain consistency.

runtimeType.name: runtimeType
runtimeType.comment: A representation of the runtime type of the object.

==.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all dart-core.Objects is to return true if and only if this and analyzer/analyzer.ErrorType.==.other are the same object.

Override this method to specify a different equality relation on a class. The overriding method must still be an equivalence relation. That is, it must be:

  • Total: It must return a boolean for all arguments. It should never throw or return null.

  • Reflexive: For all objects o, o == o must be true.

  • Symmetric: For all objects o1 and o2, o1 == o2 and o2 == o1 must either both be true, or both be false.

  • Transitive: For all objects o1, o2, and o3, if o1 == o2 and o2 == o3 are true, then o1 == o3 must be true.

The method should also be consistent over time, so equality of two objects should not change over time, or at least only change if one of the objects was modified.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override the analyzer/analyzer.ErrorType.hashCode method as well to maintain consistency.

compareTo.name: compareTo
compareTo.comment:
Compares this object to another dart-core.Comparable

Returns a value like a dart-core.Comparator when comparing this to analyzer/analyzer.ErrorType.compareTo.other. That is, it returns a negative integer if this is ordered before analyzer/analyzer.ErrorType.compareTo.other, a positive integer if this is ordered after analyzer/analyzer.ErrorType.compareTo.other, and zero if this and analyzer/analyzer.ErrorType.compareTo.other are ordered together.

The analyzer/analyzer.ErrorType.compareTo.other argument must be a value that is comparable to this object.

noSuchMethod.name: noSuchMethod
noSuchMethod.comment:
analyzer/analyzer.ErrorType.noSuchMethod is invoked when users invoke a non-existent method on an object. The name of the method and the arguments of the invocation are passed to analyzer/analyzer.ErrorType.noSuchMethod in an dart-core.Invocation. If analyzer/analyzer.ErrorType.noSuchMethod returns a value, that value becomes the result of the original invocation.

The default behavior of analyzer/analyzer.ErrorType.noSuchMethod is to throw a dart-core.NoSuchMethodError.

toString.name: toString
toString.comment: Returns a string representation of this object.
